The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Tuesday, September 09, 2003 				 Terror cloud on minister
																								Jammu, Sept. 8 (PTI): Jammu and Kashmir agriculture minister Abdul Aziz Zargar is under suspicion following disclosures by a Lashkar-e-Toiba militant who is an accused in the Akshardham temple attack case. 																								The militant has said he had taken shelter in the ministers house.																								Police have denied any connection between the minister and the Lashkar terrorists involved in the attack but a probe is on in this matter, official sources said.																								They said the ministers house at Manzgam village in south Kashmir was visited by militants like other houses for food and shelter. 																								However, the minister has the allegations. 																								He maintained that the house was not being used by him and his family. 
